{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17539280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17539280"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:39:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:39:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16566"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17619631","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17619631"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:33:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:33:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16566"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16566","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16566"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.03,0.91,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9257"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65715"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9257"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16566"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51154"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3018"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11676"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21931"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21935"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22112"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65715","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65715"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of intermittent dizziness. She describes a vague sensation of \u0027floating\u0027 and feeling \u0027spaced out\u0027 that occurs most days, lasting several hours. The symptoms are worse when she is stressed at work. She has no associated hearing loss, tinnitus, or true vertigo. She has a history of generalised anxiety disorder and takes sertraline. She does not smoke and drinks alcohol occasionally.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Neurological examination including cranial nerves, cerebellar function, and Dix-Hallpike test is normal. Her ears appear normal on otoscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her dizziness?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo","Vestibular neuritis","Functional/psychological","Orthostatic hypotension","Cerebellar dysfunction"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with chronic non-specific dizziness without clear vestibular or neurological features. The vague description, chronic course, association with stress, and normal examination findings are typical of functional dizziness. \u003Cstrong\u003EFunctional/psychological\u003C/strong\u003E causes are the most common cause of dizziness globally, accounting for approximately 30-40% of cases. These patients often describe their symptoms as a sensation of floating, lightheadedness, or feeling \u0027spaced out\u0027 rather than true vertigo.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBenign paroxysmal positional vertigo\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with brief episodes of true rotatory vertigo triggered by changes in head position. The Dix-Hallpike test would typically be positive, which is not the case here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVestibular neuritis\u003C/strong\u003E usually presents acutely with severe vertigo, nausea, and vomiting, often following a viral illness. The symptoms are typically much more severe and have a different time course than described here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOrthostatic hypotension\u003C/strong\u003E causes lightheadedness on standing that improves when lying down. The symptoms are positional and brief, unlike the prolonged symptoms described in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECerebellar dysfunction\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with ataxia, dysmetria, and other signs of cerebellar impairment on examination. The normal neurological examination makes this diagnosis unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management of functional dizziness involves addressing underlying psychological factors, reassurance about the benign nature of the symptoms, and potentially cognitive behavioural therapy. Some patients may benefit from vestibular rehabilitation exercises.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Functional/psychological causes are the most common cause of dizziness globally, accounting for approximately 30-40% of cases.","A thorough history is essential to differentiate between vertigo, presyncope, disequilibrium, and non-specific dizziness.","Anxiety and depression frequently manifest with dizziness as a somatic symptom."],"references":["Habs M, Strobl R, Grill E, Dieterich M, Becker-Bense S. Primary or secondary chronic functional dizziness: does it make a difference? A DizzyReg study in 356 patients. J Neurol. 2020 Dec;267(Suppl 1):212-222. doi: 10.1007/s00415-020-10150-9. Epub 2020 Aug 27. PMID: 32852579; PMCID: PMC7718176.","Breinbauer HA, Ar\u00e9valo-Romero C, Villarroel K, Lavin C, Fa\u00fandez F, Garrido R, Alarc\u00f3n K, Stecher X, Zamorano F, Billeke P, Delano PH. Functional Dizziness as a Spatial Cognitive Dysfunction. Brain Sci. 2023 Dec 23;14(1):16. doi: 10.3390/brainsci14010016. PMID: 38248231; PMCID: PMC10813051.","Dieterich M, Staab JP, Brandt T. Functional (psychogenic) dizziness. Handb Clin Neurol. 2016;139:447-468. doi: 10.1016/B978-0-12-801772-2.00037-0. PMID: 27719862.","Dieterich M, Staab JP. Functional dizziness: from phobic postural vertigo and chronic subjective dizziness to persistent postural-perceptual dizziness. Curr Opin Neurol. 2017 Feb;30(1):107-113. doi: 10.1097/WCO.0000000000000417. PMID: 28002123."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51154"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16566"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51154","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51154"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-26T17:50:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-29T10:20:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9257"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65715"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"